comments.body:
@joeyaiello I am actually pointing out that when the installation technology is MSI - you don't have any other choice than to do an installer file per-bitness.

However, even if you did setup.exe, probably still best to have 2 because the only way to make one is to make the wrapper setup.exe 32-bit and Nano and many installations of Server Core won't have the 32-bit subsystem installed.

FYI - chocolatey handles the switch between bitness specific installers transparently.
